ing factor for Product T\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The contribution per unit of limiting factor for Product T is calculated as $17.33 per kg. This is derived from the formula Contribution per kg = $52 / 3. This calculation is vital for determining the profitability of Product T when resources are limited, guiding production decisions to maximize profit [Data: Concepts (1708); Relationships (1590)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Interrelationship between Product T and production constraints\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Product T is subject to the same production constraints as Product B, involving both materials and labor. This interrelationship highlights the need to balance the production of multiple products within the same resource limitations, ensuring that the overall production plan is optimized for efficiency and profitability [Data: Concepts (1701); Relationships (1589)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Total contribution from Product T in April\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The total contribution from Product T in April is calculated using simultaneous equations. This method allows for the precise determination of the contribution from Product T, considering the constraints and contributions of other products. This insight is crucial for monthly financial planning and performance evaluation [Data: Relationships (1591)].\"\n        }\n    ]\n}", "input": "\nYou are an AI assistant that helps a human analyst to perform general information discovery within a textbook. Information discovery is the process of identifying and assessing relevant information associated with certain entities (e.g., concepts, methodologies, quizzes, examples, cases) within a chapter of a textbook.\n\n# Goal\nWrite a comprehensive report of a chapter, given a list of concepts, methodologies, formulas and examples that belong to the chapter as well as their relationships and optional associated claims. The report will be u